==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pung
<hw>Pung</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <def>A kind of plain sleigh drawn by one horse;
originally, a rude oblong box on runners.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sledges or <qex>pungs</qex>, coarsely framed of split saplings,
and surmounted with a large crockery crate.</q> <rj><qau>
Judd.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They did not take out the <qex>pungs</qex> to-day.</q> <rj><qau>
E. E. Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pungence</ent>⟦br⟧
